OL,3,C'You should never come that close to
OL,4,Cdeath': Louise Thompson recalls son's
OL,5,Cbirth
OL,7,FAfter Louise was discharged from
OL,8,Fhospital, she had another bleed at
OL,9,Fhome where she lost more than five
OL,10,Flitres of blood in the middle of the
OL,11,Fnight. The second harrowing incident
OL,12,Fleft Louise with PTSD and unable to
OL,13,Fcarry another pregnancy, a choice that
OL,14,Fhas now been taken away from her.JWhen
OL,15,FI asked Louise what the impact of the
OL,16,Fbirth had on her life, she replied:
OL,17,F"Everything, for a period of time,
OL,18,Feverything in my life was destroyed by
OL,19,Fmy birth."
