OL,3,C'You should never come that close to
OL,4,Cdeath': Louise Thompson recalls son's
OL,5,Cbirth
OL,7,F'I was the poster girl for health and
OL,8,Fyou never think it's going to happen
OL,9,Fto you'
OL,11,FThroughout her recovery, Louise found
OL,12,Fit difficult to talk about her
OL,13,Ftraumatic birth. She found comfort in
OL,14,Fwriting and her first book "Lucky" is
OL,15,Freleased on Thursday.
OL,17,FIn the aftermath, Louise said she felt
OL,18,Flike the "unluckiest person" but
OL,19,Fduring her recovery she started
OL,20,F"shifting the narrative" to "focus on
OL,21,Fthe good stuff".
