OL,3,C'You should never come that close to
OL,4,Cdeath': Louise Thompson recalls son's
OL,5,Cbirth
OL,7,F"I did start to see more of the
OL,8,Fpositives in life: I felt lucky for
OL,9,Fliving close to a hospital, for
OL,10,Flooking after myself my whole life, so
OL,11,Fthat my body was able to recover, and
OL,12,Ffor having a healthy son that survived.
OL,14,F"Obviously for surviving myself too,
OL,15,Fhaving a partner and having family
OL,16,Fclose by and just being really, really
OL,17,Fgrateful for those things, because I
OL,18,Fknow that there are a lot of people
OL,19,Fthat are less fortunate. That that's
OL,20,Fwhy I feel lucky, because I'm here."
