OL,3,C'You should never come that close to
OL,4,Cdeath': Louise Thompson recalls son's
OL,5,Cbirth
OL,7,FDespite everything, Louise says she
OL,8,Fdoes feel lucky. She believes the
OL,9,Frelationship she has with Leo has been
OL,10,Fstrengthened by the tough start they
OL,11,Fhad. But he is also lucky that his mum
OL,12,Fis alive.
OL,14,F"I will never get that time back with
OL,15,Fmy son that I lost in the beginning
OL,16,Fand equally I will have to live with
OL,17,FPTSD for the rest of my life," Louise
OL,18,Fsaid.
OL,20,F"It's not something you can cure. It's
OL,21,Fnot going to disappear."
